coremeta4cat:SYNTH_002_coprecipitation_method a VOC4CAT:0007016 ;
    dcterms:description "aqueous solutions of Ni(NO3)2 (0.5 M) and Ce(NO3)3 (0.5 M) mixed in stoichiometric ratio; precipitant: 1 M Na2CO3 solution added dropwise at 2 mL/min; target pH 8.5 maintained by feedback addition; mixing: 600 rpm mechanical stirring at 60 deg C for 2 h; aging: 12 h at 60 deg C without stirring; filtration: vacuum filtration through Whatman grade 4 filter paper; washing: 5 successive deionized water washes until conductivity < 5 uS/cm (Na+ removal); drying: 120 deg C for 12 h in static air oven; calcination: 5 deg C/min ramp to 500 deg C, isothermal hold for 4 h in static air, natural cooling" ;
    dcterms:title "co-precipitation" .

